NUMBER 2645
NAME Eliditur Tower, training
ASTRAL
CALL 33
FIXED_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
The implements of training, ranging from archery targets on the west
wall to a table filled with steel blocks, upon which a Psionicist can
hone his skills, are neatly laid out across the breadth of this chamber.
Engraved into the northern wall, and seemingly keeping a watchful eye
on the activities within the chamber, is a stylized silver rose. On
either side of the silver rose is a silver plaque. A single
arch leads back out to the main tower.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 60 VAL2=2670
ITEM 1 400
ITEM 9 693
IFPREVERB READ 1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER Guild Rules
   ECHO PLAYER I:     The core rule of the Eliditur Fellowship is that the allegiance of individual members is known only within the Guild. Put more simply, if a member, at his/her option, decides not to publicly display their allegiance to the Guild, that right will be respected by all other members.  If someone asks you if the person in question is a member, you will answer that they are not. You will also not offer any opinions as to their allegiance if not asked.
   ECHO PLAYER        This rule exists to protect the members of the Guild as well as to allow certain members a greater amount of freedom in their actions relating to non-Guildmembers.
   ECHO PLAYER II:    Guildmembers will not associate with followerss of the Dark solely for convenience.  This includes hunting, usage of secondary abilities and training.  If there is a good reason for the association, this rule may be ignored.  In all other circumstances, please adhere to this.
   ECHO PLAYER III:   Sorcerous Summons and Sorcerous Summons II.  These two conjurations spells have no real 'Good' use and should be taught to non-Guildmembers only if the trainee is clearly a follower of the Light.
   ECHO PLAYER IV:    Dark Necromancy:  Members of Eliditur will not use or propagate the spells that belong to the realm of Dark Necromancy.
   ECHO PLAYER V:     Non-member access to the Island:  Guildmembers are welcome to bring guests to any part of the Island except for the training area. Also, keep in mind that non-members can not leave without your help - please don't leave anyone stranded.
   ECHO OTHERS %N reads the plaque.
ENDIF
